      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the<strong> sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> (skin on) into wedges and add to a large bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>sweet potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray and put them in the oven for 20-25 min or until the wedges are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
